SECTION 4.6 - TRAINING

      All officers shall receive training, at least bi-monthly, on the Department's use of force policy and related legal updates.

      In addition, training shall be provided on a regular and periodic basis and designed to: provide techniques for the use of and 
      reinforce the importance of de-escalation; simulate actual shooting situations and conditions; and reinforce the appropriate 
      exercise ofdiscretion and judgment in using less-than-lethal and deadly force in accordance with this policy.

      Furthermore all use-of-force training shall be documented.
